IBB Law The Bury, Church St, Chesham, Buckinghamshire, HP5 1JE
CONTRACT (LEASEHOLD)

Incorporating the Standard Conditions of Sale (Fifth Edition) – 2018 Revision

Date:

Seller: Jennifer Joan Yates of 49 Duke Street Windsor SL4 1SH and Russell John Hallam of Capital Court 30 Windsor Street Uxbridge UB8 1AB as Executors of the late Mary Elizabeth Housley

Buyer: Eveele Limited (Company Number 12998675)
[Note: Original buyer M Maun and S Suri Maun of 101 Grosvenor Crescent Hillingdon Middlesex UB10 9EU was crossed out]

Property: All that leasehold property known as 34 Fairfield Road Uxbridge UB8 1AL and Garage 34 is held for the residue of the term of the registered lease dated 19 February 2004 made between (1) Royle Estates (Hoddesdon) Limited and (2) Mary Elizabeth Housley.

Title Number: AGL126671

Specified Incumbrances: The matters contained or referred to in the Property Register and Entry number 1 of the Charges Register of the above title as disclosed by the Official Copy of Register Entries dated 26th August 2020 at 09:26:13. The rent reserved by and the covenants contained in the registered lease.

Title guarantee: Limited Title Guarantee

Completion date: The day of

Contract rate: 4% above National Westminster Bank Plc base rate from time to time in force

Purchase price: £295,000.00

Deposit: £29,500.00

Contents price (if separate):

Balance:

The Seller will sell and the Buyer will buy the property for the purchase price.

SPECIAL CONDITIONS

1. (a) This contract incorporates the Standard Conditions of Sale (Fifth Edition) – 2018 Revision.
   (b) The terms used in this contract have the same meaning when used in the Conditions.

2. Subject to the terms of this contract and to the Standard Conditions of Sale, the Seller is to transfer the property with either full title guarantee or limited title guarantee, as specified on the front page.

3. (a) The sale includes those contents which are indicated on the attached list as included in the sale and the Buyer is to pay the contents price for them.
   (b) The sale excludes those fixtures which are at the property and are indicated on the attached list as excluded from the sale.

4. The property is sold with vacant possession.

5. Representations: Neither party can rely on any representation made by the other, unless made in writing by the other or his conveyancer, but this does not exclude liability for fraud or recklessness.

6. Occupier's consent: Each occupier identified below agrees with the Seller and the Buyer, in consideration of their entering into this contract, that the occupier concurs in the sale of the property on the terms of this contract, undertakes to vacate the property on or before the completion date and release the property and any included fixtures and contents from any right or interest that the occupier may have.
Note: this condition does not apply to occupiers under leases or tenancies subject to which the property is sold.
Name(s) and signature(s) of the occupier(s) (if any):
Name:
Signature:

7. The Property is sold with limited title guarantee, save that the covenant implied by section 3(3) of the Law of Property (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1994 shall apply as far as it relates to the actions or omissions of the Seller only to the period since the date of death of Mary Elizabeth Housley on the 08/01/2020 and a suitable clause shall be inserted in the Transfer Deed to this effect.

8. Subject to Standard Condition 7.2.3 if the sale shall be completed after the latest time for completion the party in default shall be liable to the other for loss including additional expenses incurred by and occasioned to that person by reason of such delay including the costs of concluding the Seller's related transaction (if any).

9. If notice to complete is required under Standard Condition 6.8 the defaulting party shall pay the other party's Solicitors additional costs of £100 plus VAT for the preparation and service of the notice.

10. If the deposit actually paid upon exchange of contracts shall be less than 10% of the total of the purchase price and the chattels price then notwithstanding the acceptance by the Seller of a lesser amount by way of deposit the balance of 10% shall at all times remain due to the Seller and in the event of rescission or failure to complete (through no fault of the Seller) such balance shall be a legal liability of the Buyer to the Seller as a condition of this contract.

11. The Property is sold in its present state of repair and condition and the assignment or transfer to the Buyer will contain a declaration that no covenant will be implied by statute which would make the Seller liable for any breach of the terms of the lease concerning the repair condition and/or decoration of the Property.

12. The Seller's Solicitors will not accept payments of the deposit and/or completion funds unless these are remitted to IBB Law LLP direct from the client account of the Buyer's Solicitors which has been previously supplied to IBB Law LLP and approved with the Vendor Law Firm Search. The Buyer's Solicitors will not arrange payments into IBB Law LLP client account by any third parties whatsoever unless this has been agreed by IBB Law LLP in writing. This special condition will not merge and become extinguished upon completion.

Notices may be sent to:

Seller's Conveyancers Name: IBB Law LLP, The Bury, Church Street, Chesham, HP5 1JE

Buyer's Conveyancers Name: Foot Anstey LLP, The Quad, Blackbrook Park Avenue, Taunton, TA1 2PX
